The Willow Flycatcher here are not at a swamp or riparian area.  There is 17 year old forest regrowth after a forest fire in 2003.  The location is the slope of a ridge in the Rocky Mountains.  There are interspered willow vegetation and some openings, but it is all dry.  Seems unusual for habitat for them.
